uk.recurse.bitwrapper.annotation

Annotation Type Bytes


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Bytes
    Declares the bytes that the annotated method should return when it is invoked. The ByteBuffer passed into the decoder function will be a view of the underlying data in order to avoid unnecessary data copying. Offset and length expressions take precedence over literal values when both are declared.
    See Also:
    Bits

        An expression to be evaluated that returns the offset. Expressions can refer other methods on the class and can use standard boolean and arithmetic operators, for example: crc() == 1 ? length() + 4 : length().
